"{\"chatHistory\":[{\"text\":\"Hello! How can I assist you today?\",\"sender\":\"ai\"},{\"text\":\"help me create a ppt on my mm project\",\"sender\":\"user\"},{\"text\":\"## Creating a PowerPoint Presentation for Your MM Project\\n\\n### Slide 1: Title Slide  \\n- **Title:** 8051 Project: ASCII to Morse Code Converter  \\n- **Subtitle:** A detailed overview of the project  \\n- **Your Name**  \\n- **Date**  \\n\\n### Slide 2: Problem Statement  \\n- **Objective:** Convert ASCII alphabet to Morse code on port 0 of the 8051 microcontroller.\\n- **Significance:** Understanding Morse code and its applications in communication.\\n\\n### Slide 3: Algorithm Overview  \\n- **Lookup Table (LUT):** Used to compare and find the equivalent Morse code value.  \\n- **ASCII Conversion:** Subtract 41H from the ASCII value to find the equivalent Morse code.\\n- **Morse Code Representation:**  \\n  - Dot (.) = 01  \\n  - Dash (-) = 11  \\n\\n### Slide 4: Key Components  \\n- **EXCHANGING DPTR Subroutine:** Manages the exchange of DPTR values with temporary registers.  \\n- **Data Handling:** Switches between accessing the LUT and the input string without losing track of addresses.\\n\\n### Slide 5: Morse Code Representation  \\n- **Example:**  \\n  - Letter 'A' is represented as `.-`  \\n  - Binary Sequence: `0111`  \\n  - Stored in LUT at index corresponding to 'A'.\\n\\n### Slide 6: Code Snippet  \\n```assembly\\nORG 0H  \\nSTART: MOV DPTR, #LUT  ; Set DPTR to the lookup table (LUT) address  \\nACALL EXCHANGINGDPTR  ; Exchange DPTR with temporary registers  \\nMOV DPTR, #DATATOCONVERT  ; Set DPTR to the address of the data to convert  \\nNEXT_CHAR:\\n```\\n\\n### Slide 7: Conclusion  \\n- **Summary:** The project successfully converts ASCII characters to Morse code using the 8051 microcontroller.\\n- **Future Work:** Explore additional features or optimizations for the converter.\\n\\n### Slide 8: Questions  \\n- **Open Floor:** Invite questions from the audience.\",\"sender\":\"a